1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================
"Entity" means any individual, company, partnership, government body, non-profit,
or other organization, together with all of its Affiliates (any entity that
controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with it). For purposes of
the Revenue Threshold, all revenues of an Entity and all of its Affiliates are
aggregated — revenues may not be divided across related entities to avoid the
Commercial License obligation.

"Annual Gross Revenue" means the total worldwide gross revenue, turnover, or
receipts of an Entity (including all Affiliates) from all sources during the
Entity's most recently completed fiscal year, expressed in United States Dollars
(USD), calculated at invoice price before discounts, returns, or inter-company
transfers, and inclusive of revenue from all products, services, and deployments
in which the Software is used. For Entities with no revenue, Annual Gross Revenue
is zero. Affiliated entities' revenues are aggregated and may not be split to
remain below the Revenue Threshold.

"Revenue Threshold" means USD $100,000 in Annual Gross Revenue.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software by or for a for-profit Entity, or
any use in connection with a product, service, or internal business operation,
regardless of deployment method, whether the Software is run locally, internally,
in a pipeline, in CI, on a developer's machine, or otherwise, and regardless of
whether the Software is distributed or kept internal.

"Community Use" means any use by an Entity whose Annual Gross Revenue is below
the Revenue Threshold, and all non-commercial use (personal use, evaluation,
education, academic research, and not-for-profit use).

