This Community License covers:
  (a) any individual using the Software personally;
  (b) any Entity whose Annual Gross Revenue is below the Revenue Threshold; and
  (c) evaluation, education, academic research, and not-for-profit use.

No fee is owed while You qualify for the Community License.

================================================================================
3. COMMERCIAL LICENSE (REQUIRED AT OR ABOVE THE REVENUE THRESHOLD)
================================================================================
If an Entity's Annual Gross Revenue is at or above the Revenue Threshold and the
Entity puts the Software to Commercial Use, that Entity MUST obtain a paid
Commercial License from Licensor to install, run, or continue using the Software.

3.1  SELF-REPORTING. An Entity that crosses the Revenue Threshold while using the
     Software must notify Licensor and obtain a Commercial License within sixty
     (60) days of the end of the fiscal year in which the Threshold was crossed.
     Continued use after that cure period without a Commercial License is a
     material breach and terminates all rights under this Agreement (Section 9).

3.2  SCOPE. The Commercial License is licensed per Entity based on company size /
     revenue. It is NOT charged per seat, per user, per token, per request, or
     per unit of compute. One Entity-level license covers the Entity's permitted
     internal use.

3.3  ANNUAL REVENUE CERTIFICATION. Each Commercial Licensee must deliver to
     Licensor, within thirty (30) days after the end of each fiscal year, a
     written certification signed by an authorized officer stating the Entity's
     Annual Gross Revenue for that year and confirming continued compliance with
     this Agreement. Failure to deliver timely certification is a material breach.

3.4  AUDIT RIGHTS. Licensor (or a designated independent auditor bound by
     confidentiality) may, upon thirty (30) days' written notice and no more than
     once per calendar year, audit the books and records of any Entity using the
     Software to verify compliance with this Agreement, including but not limited
     to Annual Gross Revenue calculations. If the audit reveals an underpayment or
     unpaid Commercial License obligation exceeding ten percent (10%) of the
     amount owed, the audited Entity shall bear the reasonable cost of the audit
     in addition to the amounts owed. Audit records are kept confidential and used
     solely to verify compliance.

3.5  HOW TO OBTAIN. Contact Licensor at the address in Section 12 to obtain a
     Commercial License and current pricing.

